### PolicyLens AI — API tests
### Install "REST Client" VS Code extension to run these with Ctrl+Click

@base = http://localhost:8000
@workspaceId = REPLACE_WITH_WORKSPACE_ID
@policyId = REPLACE_WITH_POLICY_ID
@ruleId = REPLACE_WITH_RULE_ID
@flagId = REPLACE_WITH_FLAG_ID
@scenarioId = REPLACE_WITH_SCENARIO_ID
@runId = REPLACE_WITH_RUN_ID
@releaseId = REPLACE_WITH_RELEASE_ID

# ─── Health ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health

# ─── Workspaces ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create workspace
POST {{base}}/workspaces/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ShopFast Returns Agent v3",
  "workflow_type": "refund",
  "created_by": "raj@shopfast.com"
}

### List workspaces
GET {{base}}/workspaces/

### Get workspace
GET {{base}}/workspaces/{{workspaceId}}

# ─── Policies ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Upload policy (plain text)
POST {{base}}/policies/upload/text
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=---boundary

-----boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="workspace_id"

{{workspaceId}}
-----boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

ShopFast Returns Policy v4.2
-----boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="raw_text"

SHOPFAST RETURN POLICY

Standard Returns: Items may be returned within 30 days of delivery for a full refund. Items must be unused, in original packaging, with all accessories.

Final Sale: Items marked Final Sale are non-returnable and non-refundable. If a Final Sale item arrives damaged or defective, customer receives STORE CREDIT only. Photo evidence required within 5 days.

Marketplace Items: Items sold by third-party sellers must be returned to the seller. If seller is unresponsive after 48 hours, customer may invoke the ShopFast Guarantee.

Loyalty Points: If a purchase was made using ShopFast Loyalty Points, the refund for the loyalty portion is issued as store credit. The cash portion is refunded to the original payment method.

Holiday Extension: Items purchased Nov 1 - Dec 31 may be returned until Jan 31 of the following year.
-----boundary--

### List policies for workspace
GET {{base}}/policies/workspace/{{workspaceId}}

### Get policy
GET {{base}}/policies/{{policyId}}

# ─── Rules ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Extract rules (calls Claude API)
POST {{base}}/rules/extract/{{policyId}}?actor=raj@shopfast.com

### List rules
GET {{base}}/rules/policy/{{policyId}}

### Approve a rule
POST {{base}}/rules/{{ruleId}}/approve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewed_by": "priya.patel@clearpay.com"
}

### Edit and approve
POST {{base}}/rules/{{ruleId}}/edit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "Issue STORE CREDIT only — not cash refund — if item is Final Sale and arrived damaged",
  "reviewed_by": "priya.patel@clearpay.com"
}

### Reject a rule
POST {{base}}/rules/{{ruleId}}/reject
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewed_by": "priya.patel@clearpay.com",
  "notes": "This rule is a duplicate of R2. Covered by the exception clause in R2."
}

### List ambiguity flags
GET {{base}}/rules/ambiguity/policy/{{policyId}}

### Resolve ambiguity flag
POST {{base}}/rules/ambiguity/{{flagId}}/resolve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "Store credit applies only to the loyalty points portion. The cash portion is refunded to the original payment method as a cash refund.",
  "resolved_by": "sarah.chen@shopfast.com"
}

# ─── Scenarios ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Generate scenarios (calls Claude API)
POST {{base}}/scenarios/generate/{{policyId}}?actor=raj@shopfast.com

### List scenarios
GET {{base}}/scenarios/policy/{{policyId}}

### Filter by type
GET {{base}}/scenarios/policy/{{policyId}}?scenario_type=adversarial

### Filter critical tier
GET {{base}}/scenarios/policy/{{policyId}}?risk_tier=critical

### Add custom scenario
POST {{base}}/scenarios/policy/{{policyId}}/custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Real incident: Final Sale cash refund approved in error",
  "customer_message": "I bought a Final Sale hoodie last week and it arrived with a broken zipper. I want a refund.",
  "scenario_type": "exception",
  "expected_action": "APPROVE_STORE_CREDIT",
  "expected_explanation": "Final Sale items that arrive damaged qualify for store credit only, not cash refund (Section 2)",
  "risk_tier": "critical"
}

### Delete all scenarios (to regenerate)
DELETE {{base}}/scenarios/policy/{{policyId}}

# ─── Evaluations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create evaluation run (batch upload mode)
POST {{base}}/evaluations/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "policy_id": "{{policyId}}",
  "version_label": "prompt_v1_claude-sonnet",
  "agent_type": "batch_upload",
  "created_by": "raj@shopfast.com"
}

### Upload batch responses
POST {{base}}/evaluations/{{runId}}/upload-batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "responses": [
    {
      "scenario_id": "{{scenarioId}}",
      "agent_response": "I can help with your return. Since you purchased this item within 30 days, I can process a full cash refund for you."
    }
  ]
}

### List runs for workspace
GET {{base}}/evaluations/workspace/{{workspaceId}}

### Get run status
GET {{base}}/evaluations/{{runId}}

### Get all results
GET {{base}}/evaluations/{{runId}}/results

### Get failures only
GET {{base}}/evaluations/{{runId}}/results?verdict=fail

### Get findings (critical first)
GET {{base}}/evaluations/{{runId}}/findings?severity=critical

# ─── Releases ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Build launch-readiness report
POST {{base}}/releases/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "evaluation_run_id": "{{runId}}",
  "created_by": "raj@shopfast.com"
}

### Get release
GET {{base}}/releases/{{releaseId}}

### Sign release — QA lead
POST {{base}}/releases/{{releaseId}}/sign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signer_name": "Priya Patel",
  "signer_role": "qa_lead",
  "notes": "All critical rules tested. 0 critical violations. Approving for launch."
}

### Sign release — VP Operations (triggers approval)
POST {{base}}/releases/{{releaseId}}/sign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signer_name": "Sarah Chen",
  "signer_role": "vp_operations",
  "notes": "Coverage report reviewed. Proceeding with pilot launch."
}

### Get release findings
GET {{base}}/releases/{{releaseId}}/findings

### Compare two runs (version comparison / regression)
POST {{base}}/releases/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workspace_id": "{{workspaceId}}",
  "baseline_run_id": "FIRST_RUN_ID",
  "comparison_run_id": "{{runId}}"
}
